RadialGravityField
Welcome to Timed!
This tutorial will teach you everything you need to know to
get started!
Timed is a physic based puzzle in which the main goal is
to move objects from one place to another.
To archive that, the player has to define events which
changes the state of a effector.
Altought those events are tied to a point of time, you can
always skip to another timepoint and examine the
implications of the event. Just like watching a video!
Elements
This is a ColliderBody and the most important
Element of the Game! It basicly is a ball that
reacts with the world as you would expect and
has to reach the goal to end the level.
This is a Goal, and as you probably already
guessed the ColliderBodies have to reach it.
Also the number in the middle of it indicates
the amount if ColliderBodies which are needed to
complete the level.
Lastly there are also Walls. ColliderBodies can't
pass through them.
Effectors
As already mentioned the gameplay consists of defining
EffectorEvents. Effectors are Elements that react to in range
ColliderBodies. Each Effector has different effects on the
ColliderBody, which can range from changing its color to
directly manipulating its position.
EffectorEvents are defined by picking a execution time for
them. Once defined they can be ereased and finetuned, but
more about that later.
Also the available events might be different from level to
level.
Effectors
Here we can see the RadialGravityField. When
activated it pulls in range ColliderBodies to it's
center. Available events are turning it on,
inverting its force (therefor pushing instead of
pulling) and changing its color.
This is a ColorChanger. When a ColliderBody is
passing through the upper laser its color will
be changed to the color of the laser. Available
events are changing the lasers color.
Colors
Now you are probably thinking what are colors?
ColliderBodies do have a active color, which results in them
only interacting with Effectors that have the same color.
Therefor for example a yellow ColliderBody is not effected
by a blue RadialGravityField. However, if it would pass
throught a blue ColorChanger and afterwards enter the blue
RadialGravityField, then they would interact with each other.
The same goes for Goals. A yellow Goal will only accept
yellow ColliderBodies!
User Interface - Overview
Timeline
This is the Timeline, and its basicly like a
video player. The Timepointer shows you
in which frame you are currently in. The
Playbutton will continue the automatic
time advancement. While being in the pause
state, you can manually skip to another
frame by either moving the Timepointer by
Playbutton
Timepointer
touching it, or with using the
Frameskipbuttons. Those will
either take you 1-5 Frames
backwards or forwards.
There are also Eventmarkers
that indicates the timepoints
of defined EffectorEvents.
Eventmarker
Frameskip-
button
EffectorPanel
Touching a Effector will open its EffectorPanel, which
provides its name and available events. Pressing a Event
will add it to the current point of the Timepointer, therefor
the Frame you are currently at. The game will then re-run
the simulation with the Event added and provide you with
the new ColliderBody positions. The Helpbutton will open
a window with informations about the Effector and its
Events. To close the window just press the Closebutton.
Exitbutton
Helpbutton
Available Events
EventPanel
On the right you can see the EventPanel. It
shows you all the defined EffectorEvents.
Touching the EffectorEvent will allow you
to edit the Event.
It also provides you with the Menubutton.
If you have completed the level, its icon
will change. Pressing it will open the Menu.
Exitbutton
Defined Events
Editing Mode
Pressing an already defined Event will enter the Editing Mode. It will
allow you to either delete the Event or select another Timepoint for it.
The Selected Event does now have a white Frame around it. Also a
Panel will open that prints the exact time and its icon. Lastly the
Timepointer will be locked onto the Eventmarker, which means that
selecting another time will also move the event to that time. The
Frameskipbuttons can again be used have the best possible control.
Once you are pleased with the new
selected time you can press the
Selected Event in the EventPanel again
and the new time was saved.
Removebutton
Selected Event
Main Menu
Last but not least the Main Menu. It shows you information
about the level such as the name, the difficulty and the
gravity. It also provides Buttons to return to the Start Sceen,
to reset the Level or when the level was complete to get to
the next Level.
The Gravity pointer will show
you the direction and the
multiplier next to it how strong
it is in reference to earths
gravity. The Difficulty is in stars
ranging from 1 to 5.
That was it! Now have fun
playing the game!
